data.title: Blake Dietrick Stats, Height, Weight, Position, Draft Status and More
data.meta_description: Checkout the latest stats of Blake Dietrick. Get info about her position, age, height, weight, draft status, shoots, school and more on WNBA.com
data.text:
About Blake

Position: Guard

Height: 5-10

Weight: 169

Birthdate: July 19, 1993

College: Princeton

Hometown: Wellesley, MA

WNBA Transactions: Signed a training camp contract with Washington on April 23, 2015. Signed a training camp contract with Los Angeles on June 3, 2015. Signed a training camp contract with Seattle on February 18, 2016, converted contract on May 13, 2016. Waived by Seattle on June 25, 2016. Signed second 7-day contract with San Antonio on July 12, 2016. Signed a training camp contract with Atlanta on March 9, 2018, converted contract on May 17, 2018. Re-signed to training camp contract with Atlanta on February 1, 2019. Signed with Seattle on June 5, 2019. Converted training camp contract with Atlanta on February 23, 2020. Signed a rest-of-season contract with Atlanta on August 24, 2021.

2021 Highlights with Atlanta:

Signed a rest-of-season contract with Atlanta on August 24, played in all nine remaining games in 2021.

Recorded a season-high 8 points in her season debut against Chicago (8/24), adding on 2 rebounds, 2 assists and a steal.

Season-best 3 rebounds, 3 assists and 2 steals at Dallas (9/2) in a season-most 27 minutes.

Recorded 2 offensive rebounds at Washington (9/10).

2020 Highlights with Atlanta:

Appeared in all 22 games and started in four.

Set the Dream’s franchise record for three point percentage with 44.8% shooting.

Saw career-best numbers in every single statistical category, finishing with 5.9 points and 3.4 assists per game.

Led the team with a career-high six assists against Connecticut (8/10).

Played all 40 minutes in her second career start, finishing with career-high records of 16 points and five rebounds against Seattle (8/12), sinking four three-pointers and shooting 6-of-12 from the field.

Dished out at least five assists on nine occasions, including a career-best 7 against Phoenix (8/14).

Scored in double figures six times with two outings of 15+ points.

2019 Highlights with Seattle:

Signed with Storm on June 5 after appearing in three preseason games with Atlanta

Appeared in first game on June 9, four days after joining team… made first career start on June 16 at Connecticut

Dished out season-high 4 assists in 8 minutes of action on Aug. 16 at Connecticut

First made field goal was a buzzer-beater in a loss to Los Angeles on Sept. 5

2018 Highlights with Atlanta:

Played in 26 games, averaging 7.2 minutes per game

Scored a season-high 12 points against Chicago (6/27), and added four rebounds and went 3-3 from the line

2016 Highlights with Seattle and San Antonio:

Joined Seattle Storm on a training camp contract, appearing in two games

Signed 7-day contract with San Antonio Stars, appearing in one game

Overseas Competition:

2015-16: Cestistica Orvieto, Italy

2016-17: Bendigo Spirit, Australia

2017-18: AO Dafni Agioy Dimitriou, Greece

2018-19: Lointek Gernika Bizkaia, Spain

2019-20: Lointek Gernika Bizkaia, Spain

College Highlights:

Named the 2014-15 Ivy League Player of the Year as a senior

Chosen as an All-American honorable mention by the Associated Press and Women’s Basketball Coaches Association after senior season

Named to the All-Ivy League first team as a junior in 2013-14

Led the Ivy League in assists her senior season (4.9 per game) while setting the Tigers single-season assists record with 157

Scored a career-high 28 points vs. Yale on 2/15/14

Personal:

Daughter of Steve and Martha Dietrick; has a younger brother Tucker

Is also a former lacrosse and cross country athlete

Majored in English at Princeton

Guided Wellesley High School to an 84-9 record in her career

Became Wellesley’s all-time leading scorer, male or female, with 1,440 points
